window.bookSummaryJSON = "<b>❖ I escaped every monster they threw at me. Then I met the one I couldn’t leave. ❖</b><br><br>I was born in blood and betrayal—trained to be a bride, raised to be a weapon, destined to be a warning.<br>But I chose freedom over obedience.<br>I vanished. Changed my name.<br>Built a life out of lies and quiet.<br><b>Until <i>he</i> found me</b>.<br><b>Rocco Calderón.</b><br><br>The Silvestri Syndicate’s enforcer.<br>Cold.<br>Controlled.<br>Ruthless in a way that feels almost holy.<br>He doesn’t ask questions.<br>He just watches—like he already knows every sin I’ve ever tried to bury.<br>I thought I could outrun my past.<br>Outwit the empire that created me.<br>But he doesn’t want my surrender.<br>He wants my secrets.<br>My scars.<br>My soul.<br><br>I should disappear again.<br>I should run.<br>But when his hands are on me, I forget how.<br>Because some cages don’t need bars.<br>And some savages don’t need chains.<br><b>They just need someone who’s wild enough to love them.</b><br>"; 
